File List
Here is a list of all documented files with brief descriptions:
 nor_flash.hThis file contains the interfaces present in the Nor Flash Library. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 qspi_cmd_init.hThis file contains the API to get the Flash Info and Initialize different flashes
 qspi_flash.hThis file contains the interfaces present in the QSPI Flash Library. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_lib.hThis file contains the interfaces present in the Secondary Bootloader(SBL) Library. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_lib_board.hThis file contains the board related interfaces like pin mux APIs, etc. present in the Secondary Bootloader(SBL) Library. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_lib_config.hThis file contains compile time configurable parameters of TDAxxx SBL. This can be used to port SBL to custom use case
 sbl_lib_tda2xx.hThis file contains the interfaces present in the Secondary Bootloader(SBL) Library valid for TDA2xx SOC family (TDA2xx and TDA2Ex platform). This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_lib_tda3xx.hThis file contains the interfaces present in the Secondary Bootloader(SBL) Library valid only for TDA3xx platform. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_utils_common.hThis file contains the SBL Utility layer common for all platforms. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_utils_ddr_config.hThis file contains the SBL Utility layer specific to TDAxx DDR configuration. This is taken from gel and follows the Gel coding guidelines which are different from starterware coding guidelines
 sbl_utils_tda2xx.hThis file contains the SBL Utility layer specific to TDA2xx SOC family. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_utils_tda3xx.hThis file contains the SBL Utility layer specific to TDA3xx platform. This also contains some related macros, structures and enums
 sbl_utils_tda3xx_i2c.hThis file contains the SBL Utility layer specific to TDA3xx platform needed for I2C communication
